articles.title: US could hike tariffs if China backtracks on rare earths: Bessent
articles.content: "The Chinese have cornered the market (on rare earths) and, unfortunately, at times they proved to be unreliable partners," Bessent told Fox News. The suspension was announced following recent talks between Trump and his Chinese counterpart Xi Jinping in South Korea. Some of the export restrictions previously decided by Beijing remain in place.
